segment.source: File Type Association Results Pane
segment.target: File Type Association Results Pane

segment.source: The File AssociationResults pane is one level below the System pane in the Application Virtualization Client Management Console, and it displays a list of the available file type associations.
segment.target: The File AssociationResults pane is one level below the System pane in the Application Virtualization Client Management Console, and it displays a list of the available file type associations.

segment.source: Users can see a list of file type extensions and the applications to which they correspond.
segment.target: Users can see a list of file type extensions and the applications to which they correspond.

segment.source: To display specific options for file types, right-click any application extension to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.
segment.target: To display specific options for file types, right-click any application extension to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.

segment.source: Delete
segment.target: Delete

segment.source: Deletes the file name extension from the list and removes the association to the file type.
segment.target: Deletes the file name extension from the list and removes the association to the file type.

segment.source: Properties
segment.target: Properties

segment.source: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected application extension.
segment.target: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected application extension.

segment.source: This dialog box has two tabs:
segment.target: This dialog box has two tabs:

segment.source: The General tab displays general information about the file type association, including the application icon and name:
segment.target: The General tab displays general information about the file type association, including the application icon and name:

segment.source: Icon—Displays the selected icon for the associated file type.
segment.target: Icon—Displays the selected icon for the associated file type.

segment.source: Association Name—Displays the name of the file type.
segment.target: Association Name—Displays the name of the file type.

segment.source: Change Icon—Click this button to change the icon for the file type association.
segment.target: Change Icon—Click this button to change the icon for the file type association.

segment.source: Extension—Displays the extension or extensions associated with a particular file type.
segment.target: Extension—Displays the extension or extensions associated with a particular file type.

segment.source: Unlink—This button is enabled when more than one extension is associated with an application.
segment.target: Unlink—This button is enabled when more than one extension is associated with an application.

segment.source: Click Unlink to manage the file type extension separately from the extension it is currently linked with.
segment.target: Click Unlink to manage the file type extension separately from the extension it is currently linked with.

segment.source: Specified application—Select this radio button, and choose an application from the drop-down list of available applications.
segment.target: Specified application—Select this radio button, and choose an application from the drop-down list of available applications.

segment.source: You are changing the application that is used by the default action.
segment.target: You are changing the application that is used by the default action.

segment.source: You can also browse to find an application if it isn't available on the drop-down list.
segment.target: You can also browse to find an application if it isn't available on the drop-down list.

segment.source: OSD file—Select this radio button, and specify a path to an Open Software Descriptor (OSD) file.
segment.target: OSD file—Select this radio button, and specify a path to an Open Software Descriptor (OSD) file.

segment.source: You can also browse to an OSD file.
segment.target: You can also browse to an OSD file.

segment.source: The Advanced tab displays detailed information about the file type association:
segment.target: The Advanced tab displays detailed information about the file type association:

segment.source: Action—Displays a list of the available actions for the associated file type.
segment.target: Action—Displays a list of the available actions for the associated file type.

segment.source: Content Type—Displays a description of the contents of the file type.
segment.target: Content Type—Displays a description of the contents of the file type.

segment.source: If this field is left blank, the client will fill it.
segment.target: If this field is left blank, the client will fill it.

segment.source: Perceived Type—Displays the file type.
segment.target: Perceived Type—Displays the file type.

segment.source: You can select one of the options from the drop-down list or add your own.
segment.target: You can select one of the options from the drop-down list or add your own.

segment.source: Confirm open after download—Select this check box to display a confirmation message after a file is loaded.
segment.target: Confirm open after download—Select this check box to display a confirmation message after a file is loaded.

segment.source: If this box is selected, when you attempt to open a file of this type by downloading it into a Web browser, the browser prompts you to see whether you want to save the file rather than open it directly into the browser without confirmation.
segment.target: If this box is selected, when you attempt to open a file of this type by downloading it into a Web browser, the browser prompts you to see whether you want to save the file rather than open it directly into the browser without confirmation.

segment.source: Always show extension—Select this check box to specify that extensions should be shown even when the user requests that the system should hide extensions for known file types.
segment.target: Always show extension—Select this check box to specify that extensions should be shown even when the user requests that the system should hide extensions for known file types.

segment.source: Add to new menu—Select this check box to specify that the extension or extensions should be listed in the shell's New context menu.
segment.target: Add to new menu—Select this check box to specify that the extension or extensions should be listed in the shell's New context menu.

segment.source: Apply to all users—Select this check box to specify that extensions should be available to all users.
segment.target: Apply to all users—Select this check box to specify that extensions should be available to all users.

segment.source: Help
segment.target: Help

segment.source: Displays the Client Management Console help system.
segment.target: Displays the Client Management Console help system.

segment.source: To display general options for the Results pane, right-click anywhere in the Results pane to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.
segment.target: To display general options for the Results pane, right-click anywhere in the Results pane to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.

segment.source: New Association
segment.target: New Association

segment.source: This menu item displays the New Association Wizard.
segment.target: This menu item displays the New Association Wizard.

segment.source: This wizard consists of two pages:
segment.target: This wizard consists of two pages:

segment.source: Enter a new or existing file name extension, and associate the extension with a file type:
segment.target: Enter a new or existing file name extension, and associate the extension with a file type:

segment.source: Extension—Enter a new file name extension.
segment.target: Extension—Enter a new file name extension.

segment.source: This field is blank by default.
segment.target: This field is blank by default.

segment.source: Create a new file type with this description—Select this radio button to enter a new file type description in the active field.
segment.target: Create a new file type with this description—Select this radio button to enter a new file type description in the active field.

segment.source: This button is selected by default, and the active field is blank.
segment.target: This button is selected by default, and the active field is blank.

segment.source: Apply this file type to all users—Select this check box when you want this association to be global for all users.
segment.target: Apply this file type to all users—Select this check box when you want this association to be global for all users.

segment.source: By default, this box is not selected.
segment.target: By default, this box is not selected.

segment.source: Link this extension with an existing file type—Select this radio button to associate the extension with an existing file type.
segment.target: Link this extension with an existing file type—Select this radio button to associate the extension with an existing file type.

segment.source: Pick a file type from the drop-down list.
segment.target: Pick a file type from the drop-down list.

segment.source: When you choose this option, Next is changed to Finish.
segment.target: When you choose this option, Next is changed to Finish.

segment.source: Select the application that will open files with the specified extension:
segment.target: Select the application that will open files with the specified extension:

segment.source: Open files with the selected application—Select this radio button to open the file with an existing application.
segment.target: Open files with the selected application—Select this radio button to open the file with an existing application.

segment.source: Choose an application from the drop-down list of available applications.
segment.target: Choose an application from the drop-down list of available applications.

segment.source: Open file with the association described in this OSD file—Select this radio button to specify an OSD file that determines the application used to open the file.
segment.target: Open file with the association described in this OSD file—Select this radio button to specify an OSD file that determines the application used to open the file.

segment.source: Use the browse button to select an existing location, or enter a path or HTTP-formatted URL in this field.
segment.target: Use the browse button to select an existing location, or enter a path or HTTP-formatted URL in this field.

segment.source: Refresh
segment.target: Refresh

segment.source: This item refreshes the Results pane.
segment.target: This item refreshes the Results pane.

segment.source: Export List
segment.target: Export List

segment.source: With this menu item, you can create a tab-delimited text file that contains the contents of the Results pane.
segment.target: With this menu item, you can create a tab-delimited text file that contains the contents of the Results pane.

segment.source: This item displays a standard File Save dialog box where you specify the location for the text file you are creating.
segment.target: This item displays a standard File Save dialog box where you specify the location for the text file you are creating.

segment.source: View
segment.target: View

segment.source: This pop-up list of menu item lets you change the appearance and content of the Results pane.
segment.target: This pop-up list of menu item lets you change the appearance and content of the Results pane.

segment.source: Arrange/Line Up Icons
segment.target: Arrange/Line Up Icons

segment.source: These menu items can be used to change how the icons are displayed in the Results pane.
segment.target: These menu items can be used to change how the icons are displayed in the Results pane.
